Several traders in the North Rift region are counting losses after properties worth millions was demolished by the Kenya Railways Company for encroaching on public land.
The businesses on Kenya Railway land in Nakuru, Eldoret, Kitale and Bungoma were destroyed to pave way for renovation of the old-meter gauge railway.



